items.title: University of Arizona donors continue $200M-plus trend
items.summary:
For the fourth year in a row, donors gave or pledged more than $200 million to the University of Arizona. With $264.7 million in gifts and commitments, fiscal 2017 was the second-highest fundraising year in University history. In fiscal 2015, the total was $293.5 million.Â  “Steadfast generosity continues to make the UA a better and more accessible university,” said John-Paul Roczniak, vice president of development and chief development officer for the UA and president and!
